## Rollback triggers

When the user writes any of the following (in any language):
- **"откати"** / **"откат"** / **"отмени"** / **"верни назад"**
- **"rollback"** / **"revert"** / **"undo last"** / **"go back"**
- **"не то"** / **"не так"** / **"верни как было"**

→ **Immediately run:**

```bash
git log --oneline -5
```

Show the last 5 commits, then ask the user **which commit** to roll back to (or assume the last one if not specified), then run:

```bash
# Soft rollback (keeps changes in working directory)
git reset --soft HEAD~1

# OR hard rollback (completely removes changes)
git reset --hard HEAD~1

# OR revert a specific commit (safer for shared branches)
git revert <commit-hash> --no-edit
```

### Rollback decision logic:
| Situation | Command |
|---|---|
| User said "откати последнее" | `git reset --soft HEAD~1` |
| User said "откати полностью" / "удали изменения" | `git reset --hard HEAD~1` |
| User specified a commit hash | `git reset --hard <hash>` |
| On shared/main branch | `git revert HEAD --no-edit` |

---

## Rules for Cursor

1. **Before every task** — check git status: `git status`
2. **After every task** — commit changes with a clear message
3. **On rollback request** — show log, confirm which commit, execute rollback
4. **Never commit** without a description
5. **Never force push** to `main` or `master` without explicit user confirmation
